26class CodeProfiler: 

27 """Generic code profiler using cProfile with categorization support.""" 

28 

29 def __init__( 

30 self, 

31 pkg_name: str, 

32 pkg_path: Path | str | None = None, 

33 module_map: dict[str, set[str]] | None = None, 

34 threshold_ms: float = 0.25, 

35 sort_mode: str | None = None, 

36 iterations: int | None = None, 

37 ) -> None: 

38 """Initialize the profiler. 

39 

40 Args: 

41 pkg_name: Name of the package to profile (e.g., "bear_shelf") 

42 pkg_path: Path to the package source. If None, auto-detected from pkg_name 

43 module_map: Maps layer names to sub paths (e.g., {"Storage": "datastore/storage/"}) 

44 threshold_ms: Filter out functions below this cumulative time in ms 

45 sort_mode: If "load_order", automatically sets threshold_ms to 0.0 

46 iterations: Number of times to run the workload function for averaging 

47 """ 

48 self.pkg_name: str = pkg_name 

49 self.pkg_path: Path = Path(pkg_path) if pkg_path is not None else self._detect_package_path() 

50 

51 self.module_map: dict[str, set[str]] = module_map or {} 

52 self.threshold_ms: float = 0.0 if sort_mode == "load_order" else threshold_ms 

53 self.stats: Stats | None = None 

54 

55 self.package_funcs: list[DebugInfo] = [] 

56 self.other_funcs: list[DebugInfo] = [] 

57 self.runtime_stats: defaultdict[LayerKey, LayerStats] = defaultdict(LayerStats) 

58 self.import_stats: defaultdict[LayerKey, LayerStats] = defaultdict(LayerStats) 

59 self.total_time: float = 0.0 

60 self.iterations: int = iterations if iterations is not None else 1 

61 self.multiple_setup_returns: bool = False 

62 self.multiple_workload_returns: bool = False 

63 

64 def _detect_package_path(self) -> Path: 

65 """Auto-detect package path from package name. 

66 

67 Returns: 

68 Path to the package source directory 

69 """ 

70 import importlib # noqa: PLC0415 

71 

72 try: 

73 pkg: ModuleType = importlib.import_module(self.pkg_name) 

74 assert pkg.__file__ is not None # noqa: S101 

75 return Path(pkg.__file__).parent 

76 except ImportError as e: 

77 raise ValueError(f"Could not import package '{self.pkg_name}': {e}") from e 

78 

79 def _categorize_by_layer(self, func_info: FuncInfo) -> str: 

80 """Categorize a function by layer based on module_map. 

81 

82 Args: 

83 func_info: Function information to categorize 

84 

85 Returns: 

86 Layer name (from module_map keys, or "Other") 

87 """ 

88 if not self.module_map: 

89 return "Other" 

90 

91 for layer, pattern in self.module_map.items(): 

92 if func_info.filename in pattern or any(p in func_info.filename for p in pattern): 

93 return layer 

94 

95 return "Other" 

96 

97 def run( 

98 self, 

99 workload_fn: Callable[..., Any], 

100 stats_file: Path | str = "profile.stats", 

101 *, 

102 setup_fn: Callable[..., Any] | None = None, 

103 teardown_fn: Callable[..., Any] | None = None, 

104 ) -> None: 

105 """Run profiling on a workload function. 

106 

107 Args: 

108 workload_fn: Function to profile (takes no args, returns nothing) 

109 stats_file: Where to save profiler stats 

110 setup_fn: Optional setup function to run before workload 

111 teardown_fn: Optional teardown function to run after workload 

112 """ 

113 import time # noqa: PLC0415 

114 

115 profiler = cProfile.Profile() 

116 

117 setup_return: Any | NotSetType = NOTSET 

118 workload_return: Any | NotSetType = NOTSET 

119 if setup_fn is not None: 

120 setup_return = setup_fn() 

121 if setup_return is not None: 

122 self.multiple_setup_returns = isinstance(setup_return, (tuple, list)) 

123 

124 start_time: float = time.perf_counter() 

125 profiler.enable() 

126 workload_return = ( 

127 workload_fn(*setup_return) 

128 if self.multiple_setup_returns 

129 else workload_fn(setup_return) 

130 if setup_return is not NOTSET 

131 else workload_fn() 

132 ) 

133 profiler.disable() 

134 end_time: float = time.perf_counter() 

135 

136 self.total_time = end_time - start_time 

137 if teardown_fn is not None: 

138 self.multiple_workload_returns = isinstance(workload_return, (tuple, list)) 

139 teardown_fn(*workload_return) if self.multiple_workload_returns else teardown_fn( 

140 workload_return 

141 ) if workload_return is not NOTSET else teardown_fn() 

142 

143 stats_path = Path(stats_file) 

144 profiler.dump_stats(str(stats_path)) 

145 

146 self.stats = Stats(str(stats_path)) 

147 self._parse_stats() 

148 

149 def _parse_stats(self) -> None: 

150 """Parse cProfile stats and categorize functions.""" 

151 if not self.stats: 

152 return 

153 

154 self.package_funcs = [] 

155 self.other_funcs = [] 

156 for func, timing in self.stats.stats.items(): # type: ignore[attr-defined] 

157 func_info = FuncInfo(*func) 

158 info = DebugInfo(func=func_info, timing=TimingInfo(*timing)) 

159 if self.pkg_name in func_info.filename: 

160 self.package_funcs.append(info) 

161 else: 

162 self.other_funcs.append(info) 

163 

164 above_threshold: list[DebugInfo] = [ 

165 info for info in self.package_funcs if info.timing.cumulative_time_ms >= self.threshold_ms 

166 ] 

167 

168 self.runtime_stats = defaultdict(LayerStats) 

169 self.import_stats = defaultdict(LayerStats) 

170 

171 for info in above_threshold: 

172 layer: str = self._categorize_by_layer(info.func) 

173 key = LayerKey(layer=layer, func_name=info.func.func_name, filename=info.func.filename) 

174 

175 if info.func.func_name == "<module>": 

176 self.import_stats[key].cumtime += info.timing.cumulative_time 

177 self.import_stats[key].tottime += info.timing.total_time 

178 self.import_stats[key].ncalls += info.timing.call_count 

179 else: 

180 self.runtime_stats[key].cumtime += info.timing.cumulative_time 

181 self.runtime_stats[key].tottime += info.timing.total_time 

182 self.runtime_stats[key].ncalls += info.timing.number_counts 

183 

184 def get_layer_totals(self) -> dict[str, LayerStats]: 

185 """Get cumulative and total times grouped by layer. 

186 

187 Returns: 

188 Dict mapping layer name to LayerStats 

189 """ 

190 layer_totals: dict[str, LayerStats] = {} 

191 for key, stats in self.runtime_stats.items(): 

192 if key.layer not in layer_totals: 

193 layer_totals[key.layer] = LayerStats() 

194 layer_totals[key.layer].cumtime += stats.cumtime 

195 layer_totals[key.layer].tottime += stats.tottime 

196 return layer_totals 

197 

198 def get_import_by_layer(self) -> dict[str, float]: 

199 """Get total import time grouped by layer. 

200 

201 Returns: 

202 Dict mapping layer name to total import time in seconds 

203 """ 

204 import_by_layer: dict[str, float] = {} 

205 for key, stats in self.import_stats.items(): 

206 if key.layer not in import_by_layer: 

207 import_by_layer[key.layer] = 0 

208 import_by_layer[key.layer] += stats.cumtime 

209 return import_by_layer 

210 

211 def get_summary_stats(self) -> SummaryStats: 

212 """Calculate summary statistics. 

213 

214 Returns: 

215 SummaryStats with all calculated metrics 

216 """ 

217 from .models import SummaryStats, TimingInfo # noqa: PLC0415 

218 

219 if not self.stats: 

220 return SummaryStats(0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0) 

221 

222 total_calls: int = sum(TimingInfo(*timing).call_count for _, timing in self.stats.stats.items()) # type: ignore[attr-defined] 

223 package_func_count: int = len(self.package_funcs) 

224 total_profiled_ms: float = self.total_time * 1000 

225 

226 import_by_layer: dict[str, float] = self.get_import_by_layer() 

227 package_import_ms: float | int = sum(import_by_layer.values()) * 1000 

228 

229 package_runtime_ms: float = sum( 

230 info.timing.total_time_ms for info in self.package_funcs if info.func.func_name != "<module>" 

231 ) 

232 package_total_ms: float = package_import_ms + package_runtime_ms 

233 dependency_ms: float = total_profiled_ms - package_total_ms 

234 

235 return SummaryStats( 

236 total_profiled_ms=total_profiled_ms, 

237 total_calls=total_calls, 

238 package_func_count=package_func_count, 

239 package_import_ms=package_import_ms, 

240 package_runtime_ms=package_runtime_ms, 

241 package_total_ms=package_total_ms, 

242 dependency_ms=dependency_ms, 

243 ) 

244 

245 def get_dependency_breakdown(self, search: str | None = None) -> dict[str, float]: 

246 """Get breakdown of time spent in external dependencies. 

247 

248 Args: 

249 search: Optional filter to show only dependencies matching this string 

250 

251 Returns: 

252 Dict mapping dependency module name to total time in ms, sorted by time 

253 """ 

254 dependency_times: dict[str, float] = {} 

255 

256 for info in self.other_funcs: 

257 module_name: str = self._extract_module_name(info.func.filename) 

258 

259 if search and search.lower() not in module_name.lower(): 

260 continue 

261 

262 if module_name not in dependency_times: 

263 dependency_times[module_name] = 0.0 

264 dependency_times[module_name] += info.timing.total_time * 1000 

265 

266 return dict(sorted(dependency_times.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)) 

267 

268 def get_dependency_funcs(self, search: str) -> list[DebugInfo]: 

269 """Get all functions from dependencies matching search string. 

270 

271 Args: 

272 search: Filter string to match against module names 

273 

274 Returns: 

275 List of DebugInfo for matching dependency functions 

276 """ 

277 matching_funcs: list[DebugInfo] = [] 

278 

279 for info in self.other_funcs: 

280 module_name: str = self._extract_module_name(info.func.filename) 

281 if search.lower() in module_name.lower(): 

282 matching_funcs.append(info) 

283 

284 return matching_funcs

286 def _extract_module_name(self, filename: str) -> str: 

287 """Extract the top-level module name from a filename. 

288 

289 Args: 

290 filename: Full file path 

291 

292 Returns: 

293 Module name (e.g., "sqlalchemy", "pydantic"), or "<builtin>" for special cases 

294 """ 

295 if filename.startswith("<") or not filename or filename == "~": 

296 return BUILTIN 

297 

298 if filename.startswith("~"): 

299 filename = str(Path(filename).expanduser()) 

300 

301 try: 

302 path_obj = Path(filename) 

303 path_parts: tuple[str, ...] = path_obj.parts 

304 

305 for i, part in enumerate(path_parts): 

306 if part == SITE_PACKAGES and i + 1 < len(path_parts): 

307 module_name: str = path_parts[i + 1] 

308 if module_name.endswith(PY_EXT): 

309 return module_name[:-3] 

310 return module_name.split(".")[0] 

311 

312 if path_obj.suffix == PY_EXT: 

313 return path_obj.stem 

314 

315 return BUILTIN 

316 except Exception: 

317 return BUILTIN
